cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.HC. 

The paper presents a method for generating timelines of events and relations for entities in a knowledge base, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) such as submodular optimization, information retrieval (cs.IR) such as web-co-occurrence statistics, and database systems (cs.DB) for handling the knowledge base. The paper also discusses user interaction and user studies, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
